        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I'm searching a way to use Zend_Auth_Adapter_Http with Database or Ldap.\nIt seems that I must made Zend_Auth_Adapter_Http_Resolver.\n\nWhat is not very logical is that Zend_Auth_Adapter_Http  should not be an adapter but only a layer above\nZend_Auth_Adapter objects. By this way it will be possible to use  any of the existing adapters like Db, OpenId or Ldap.\n\nI've tried to create Zend_Auth_Adapter_Http_Resolver_DbTable  extending Zend_Auth_Adapter_DbTable.\nIt's dirty and doesn't works because in my Db password are MD5 encoded so  resolve Method can't  return password properly\n\n"
        },
